<br>
I think NWN will be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> extremely</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> successful, but I don't think it will <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> steal</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> any of Everquest's population.  <br>
<br>
Unless you're hosting &quot;Non-stop battle server 2002&quot; whereby people make characters, go to the arena, and just hack eachother to death, or maybe &quot;Sexy tavern pub server&quot; where it's social driven story, the game doesn't have the built-in content to support logging your life away online like EQ does.<br>
<br>
People will call up their friends, say &quot;Hey, I got NWN, I put together this cool adventure, let's play all day saturday!&quot;, and they'll do just that.  But for the rest of the week, when they come home from work, or have a few hours before they have to go shopping on Sunday, or it's 4 am on a weeknight, or whatever, they'll still be loggin into EQ.<br>
<br>
Unless there's like purchasable adventures that you can just load into the game, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> someone</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is gonna have to take the time to put the adventure together.  Would be cool if it turns out you can like write adventures for people, whereby they can just load it into their NWN server and have all the orc tribes and NPCs and stuff that you made show up.  Could see a whole market of like garage run adventure design shops run by a few guys w/ some really good stories or ideas <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
